article.headline: Undefeated UC Davis beats San Jose St. 70-56
article.linkText: Undefeated UC Davis beats San Jose St. 70-56
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Josh Ritchart scored 21 points and Corey Hawkins added 20 to lead UC Davis over San Jose State 70-56 on Wednesday night. Ritchart scored 14 points in the first half as UC Davis built a 31-21 halftime lead. The Aggies opened the second half on a 10-0 run and led by double digits the rest of the way. Ritchart was 7 of 14 from the field with four 3-pointers and eight rebounds. Hawkins finished on 7-of-11 shooting. Avery Johnson and Darius Graham each had four assists for UC Davis (6-0). UC Davis never trailed, and is off to its best start in more than a century -- since the 1912-13 season, when they played just eight games to finish 7-1. It is the first victory over San Jose State since the 1974-75 season. Rashad Muhammad scored 20 points on 7-of-11 shooting to lead San Jose State (1-7).
